  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Progressive Shelter through the Swiss Red Cross</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Affected populations, Internally displaced persons (IDPs)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To meet the longer term housing needs of those displaced by the earthquake, the American Red Cross partnered with the Swiss Red Cross to upgrade transitional shelters into permanent homes. Through this partnership, the American Red Cross provided funding to improve the floors and walls of 599 transitional shelters that were already being built by the Swiss and Haitian Red Cross societies so that they can serve as permanent homes. These homes include access to basic water and sanitation, and community members were involved in the construction process, learning skills that they can apply to future jobs. The project reached 599 households in the village of Palmiste a Vin near Leogane.</narrative>
  </description>
